Grammar Terms

Russian pronouns of place names and people's names are not added for now and will be garbled in the translation above.

(accu)=accusative case,the direct object
(anim)=animated living things
(dati)=dative case,the indirect object,to who or what
(geni)=genitive case,possessive,whose things,of what
(inan)=inanimated non-living things
(impe)=imperfective verb(not complete, doing continuously)
(inst)=instrumental case, with who, by way of what
(pres)=present tense, do, does
(pass)=passive verb, is done
(past)=past verb, did
(perf)=perfective verb(complete,finished doing)
(plur)=plural
(nomi)=nominative case,the subject,as for who or what
(sing)=singular
